$Id$

These resources are helpful for writing ppc-darwin assembly:

- <http://home-1.tiscali.nl/~solognt/codingstuff/ppc_cursus.html>
  A good introduction to PPC assembly

- <http://darwinsource.opendarwin.org/10.4.6.ppc/Libc-391.2.5/ppc/sys/>
  Apple's implementation of these functions.

- <http://cvs.opendarwin.org/index.cgi/src/xnu/osfmk/ppc/hw_exception.s>
  The kernel's system call entry code - see "shandler".
  It's a little...dense...but it might be helpful.

- <http://www.securiteam.com/securityreviews/PPC_OSX_Shellcode_Assembly.pdf>
  A paper about ppc/darwin shellcode, but it has some useful small examples.

- /usr/include/architecture/ppc/reg_help.h
  Describes register usage

- /usr/incldue/architecture/ppc/asm_help.h
  Describes stack layout and has lots of helpful macros

- <http://www-106.ibm.com/developerworks/linux/library/l-ppc/>
  The "Resources" section has a good list of sites with PPC information

- <http://e-www.motorola.com/files/32bit/doc/ref_manual/MPC7450UM.pdf>
  Motorola MPC7450 RISC Microprocessor Family User's Manual
